last_episode_to_air.name: Anubis
last_episode_to_air.overview: An episode where Dewey and Vanessa sound a lot like Danny Trejo and Lance Henriksen.

name: Aqua Teen Hunger Force
overview: The surreal adventures of three anthropomorphic fast food items: Master Shake, Frylock and Meatwad, and their human nextdoor neighbor, Carl Brutananadilewski.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview:
The first season of the animated television series, Aqua Teen Hunger Force originally aired in the United States. Season one unofficially started on December 30, 2000 with the unannounced stealth airing of "Rabbot" on Cartoon Network. Season one officially began one week after the official launch of Adult Swim, on September 9, 2001 with "Escape from Leprechaupolis", and ended with "Cybernetic Ghost of Christmas Past from the Future" on December 29, 2002, with a total of eighteen episodes. This season focuses on the surreal adventures and antics of three anthropomorphic fast food items: Master Shake, Frylock, and Meatwad, who live next door to Carl Brutananadilewski in a suburban neighborhood in New Jersey.

Season one marks the first appearance of the main characters, and several recurring characters as well. Episodes in season one were written and directed by Dave Willis and Matt Maiellaro, and have either a TV-14 or a TV-PG parental rating. Almost every episode in this season features a special guest appearance, which is later continued in later seasons. This season has been made available on DVD, and other forms of home media, including on demand streaming on Netflix.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview:
The second season of the animated television series, Aqua Teen Hunger Force originally aired in the United States on Cartoon Network's late night programming block, Adult Swim. Season two started on May 25, 2003 with "Super Birthday Snake" and ended with "The Last One" on December 31, 2003, with a total of twenty four episodes. This season continues to focus on the surreal adventures and antics of three anthropomorphic fast food items: Master Shake, Frylock, and Meatwad, who live next door to Carl Brutananadilewski in a suburban neighborhood in New Jersey.

With twenty four episodes, season two is the longest season of the series so far. Episodes in season two were written and directed by Dave Willis and Matt Maiellaro, and have either a TV-14 or a TV-PG parental rating. Almost every episode in this season features a special guest appearance, including the season finale "The Last One" which features the return several guests from the first two seasons, who have reprised their roles. This season has been made available on DVD, and other forms of home media.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview:
The third season of the animated television series, Aqua Teen Hunger Force originally aired in the United States on Cartoon Network's late night programming block, Adult Swim. Season three started on April 25, 2004 with "Video Ouija" and ended with "Carl" on October 24, 2004, with a total of thirteen episodes. This season continues to focus on the surreal adventures and antics of three anthropomorphic fast food items: Master Shake, Frylock, and Meatwad, who live next door to Carl Brutananadilewski in a suburban neighborhood in New Jersey.

Season three is the only season to feature Spacecataz cold opens, in place of Dr. Weird and Steve. In season three the cold openings featuring Dr. Weird and Steve, were replaced with clips from the failed pilot Spacecataz, a potential spin-off of Aqua Teen Hunger Force. Episodes in season three were written and directed by Dave Willis and Matt Maiellaro, and have TV-14 parental rating. Almost every episode in this season features a special guest appearance, which continues a practice used in past seasons. This season has been made available on DVD, and other forms of home media.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: The fourth season of the animated television series, Aqua Teen Hunger Force originally aired in the United States on Cartoon Network's late night programming block, Adult Swim. Season four started on December 4, 2005 with "Dirtfoot" and ended with "Carl Wash" which originally made two unannounced stealth airings on December 22, 2006 and January 7, 2007 and later made its official debut on March 25, 2007, with a total of thirteen episodes.

seasons.name: Aqua TV Show Show
seasons.overview: Aqua TV Show Show (or ATSS) was the alternative title given to the tenth season of the animated television series, Aqua Teen Hunger Force. The tenth season aired in the United States on Cartoon Network's late night programming block, Adult Swim. The season started on August 11, 2013 with "Muscles" and ran for a total of ten episodes. This season focused on the surreal adventures and antics of three anthropomorphic fast food items: Master Shake, Frylock, and Meatwad, who live next door to Carl Brutananadilewski in a suburban neighborhood in the fictional location Seattle, New Jersey, which is completely identical to their other previous homes seen in past seasons. In episode 6 the skyline of Philadelphia is displayed in the background.

seasons.name: Aqua Teen Hunger Force Forever
seasons.overview: In this final installment of the fantastic adventures of Meatwad, Master Shake, Frylock and Carl, a court ruling has made divorce illegal in America. Heavily-armed, unhappy couples across the continent are tearing each other apart, and it's up to Aqua Teen Hunger Force Forever to give them the marriage counseling they need.

seasons.name: Season 12
seasons.overview: Master Shake, Frylock, and Meatwad have returned to solve all of life’s modern issues, and Carl returns because he can’t sell his crappy house because he lives next door to food.

episodes.name: Rabbot
episodes.overview: Dr. Weird proclaims he has obtained the funds to build a Rabbot to solve the world's "vegetable problem". Dr. Weird tells Steve to spray it in the eyes with French perfume and after the spraying, the Rabbot gets annoyed and escapes the lab.

episodes.name: Escape from Leprechaupolis
episodes.overview: Leprechauns use Dr. Weird's Rainbow Machine to mug people from afar, apparently for shoes. Although they don't end up with anything more than a gold chain, a Banarama tape with no case and rollerskates.

episodes.name: Bus of the Undead
episodes.overview: Dr. Weird creates a mutant moth/human called Mothmonsterman, but it flies out of the giant hole left by Rabbot and flies toward the Aqua Teen's house, craving the bright light it sees coming from within. When the light is switched off, Mothmonsterman does everything in his power to frighten Master Shake into turning it back on.

episodes.name: Balloonenstein
episodes.overview: Meatwad gets new electric powers thanks to Shake's shenanigans, which make everyone hate him because they either die or get hurt when they're near him. But it's stil useful for getting revenge on Shake.

episodes.name: Space Conflict from Beyond Pluto
episodes.overview: Frylock attempts to make contact with aliens and is successful... but there's only two problems. First, the aliens want to take over Earth, and second, they're too stupid to pull it off.

episodes.name: Ol' Drippy
episodes.overview: Shake makes a large mess in the kitchen and refuses to clean it, eventually resulting in the formation of a new lifeform which Meatwad gleefully names "Ol' Drippy".  Shake becomes jealous of the attention that the new character receives.

episodes.name: Revenge of The Mooninites
episodes.overview: The Mooninites are back and this time they've got a belt that gives them superpowers from the band Foreigner.

episodes.name: MC Pee Pants
episodes.overview: Subliminal messages in the music Meatwad has been listening to draw the team to a warehouse, where they find out that rap artist behind the music is actually a giant spider.

episodes.name: Dumber Dolls
episodes.overview: Meatwad gets a new doll, Happy Time Harry, which has a dreadfully bitter and jaded personality. Happy Time Harry's time is up when his negativity begins to affect everyone.

episodes.name: Bad Replicant
episodes.overview: Master Shake is kidnapped by returning characters Emory and Oglethorpe.  The two aliens replace him with a "replicant", but Frylock and Meatwad soon realize that the Shake "replicant" doesn't resemble Shake at all.

episodes.name: Circus
episodes.overview: Master Shake sells Meatwad to the circus, but when Meatwad becomes a huge big top success, Shake gets jealous and tries to get in on the act. It's a battle of the freaks!

episodes.name: Love Mummy
episodes.overview: Frylock discovers a mummy in the crawlspace under the house. The mummy begins to exhort his bratish favors from Frylock by threatening him with an ancient Egyptian curse.

episodes.name: Dumber Days
episodes.overview: Meatwad's brain is discovered to be nothing more than a toy with a jingle bell in it. After Meatwad goes through a brief depression, Carl gets him a new live brain against Frylock's will. With his new brain, Meatwad begins to grow smarter and larger.

episodes.name: Interfection
episodes.overview: While looking up teeth conspiracies (and Metallica) on the internet in Frylock's room, Shake and Meatwad make various popup windows appear in Frylock's room which start to spread throughout the house.

episodes.name: PDA
episodes.overview: Shake is missing his Personal Digital Assistant. The gang proceeds to look in the Adirondack mountains and in Carl's pool for it, until finally they confront the thief. If he IS a thief. Or maybe Shake's just greedy and wants his PDA.

episodes.name: Mail Order Bride
episodes.overview: As a Christmas present to themselves, Shake and Carl split the cost of a mail-order bride from Russia.  Unfortunately, once she gets a look at her new "husbands" she freaks out and locks herself in Carl's house, leaving Carl stuck outside.

episodes.name: Cybernetic Ghost of Christmas Past from the Future
episodes.overview: Carl is visited by the Cybernetic Ghost Of Christmas Past From The Future and learns that his house is built on an elfin graveyard, thus causing his pool to fill with blood. Then the Cybernetic Ghost Of Christmas Past From The Future recounts a long story about the first Christmas.

Season one unofficially started on December 30, 2000 with the unannounced stealth airing of "Rabbot" on Cartoon Network. Season one officially began one week after the official launch of Adult Swim, on September 9, 2001 with "Escape from Leprechaupolis", and ended with "Cybernetic Ghost of Christmas Past from the Future" on December 29, 2002, with a total of eighteen episodes. This season focuses on the surreal adventures and antics of three anthropomorphic fast food items: Master Shake, Frylock, and Meatwad, who live next door to Carl Brutananadilewski in a suburban neighborhood in New Jersey.

Season one marks the first appearance of the main characters, and several recurring characters as well. Episodes in season one were written and directed by Dave Willis and Matt Maiellaro, and have either a TV-14 or a TV-PG parental rating. Almost every episode in this season features a special guest appearance, which is later continued in later seasons. This season has been made available on DVD, and other forms of home media, including on demand streaming on Netflix.

episodes.name: Super Birthday Snake
episodes.overview: Meatwad asks for a bunny for his birthday, but Master Shake gets him the wrong gift... a snake! Frylock accidentally kills Meatwad and Master Shake after the snake eats them.  Free from his friends, Frylock takes up a life of crime and sex.

episodes.name: Super Hero
episodes.overview: Master Shake decides to become a superhero named "The Drizzle".  In his attempt to be noticed, he douses himself in toxic waste, hands out "Drizzle Phones" and orders a costume.

episodes.name: Super Bowl
episodes.overview: After Meatwad finds two Super Bowl tickets inside a bag of chips, everyone tries to get on his good side in order to claim the second ticket.  Soon the contest goes to Meatwad's head and he tries to take advantage of Carl and Shake.

episodes.name: Super Computer
episodes.overview: Frylock invents a new, ridiculously advanced super computer but Shake's incompetence sends it careening into Carl's house. Frylock builds another one but the advanced technologies involved accidentally send the machine back in time!

episodes.name: Super Model
episodes.overview: Master Shake comes back from a trip to Guatemala with a new nose.  With his new-found "beauty", Shake sets out to make himself the best damn looking person in the world.

episodes.name: Super Spore
episodes.overview: While The Aqua Teens are chilling in Carl's Pool one day, an alien tentacle reaches out and grabs Shake. The alien uses Shake as his method to speak with the others. The problem is, the alien only speak Japaneses. The alien is also not housebroken. Frylock takes it upon himself to civilize this new comer from space.

episodes.name: Super Sir Loin
episodes.overview: Meatwad goes on a hunger strike "For the Shorties" due to the subliminal messages in Sir Loin's new album.  However, he doesn't stop there, ravaging all the food in the house for Sir Loin's "Hunger Drive".  Something seems strangely familiar.

episodes.name: Super Squatter
episodes.overview: When Shake forgets (or decides not) to pay all the bills, all the utilities and accessories get cut off. Instead of paying the bills himself, Frylock decides to teach Shake a lesson and leaves the house with any type of utility. Shake simply takes refuge in Carl's house.

episodes.name: The Meat Zone
episodes.overview: Somehow, Meatwad develops an amazing ability to see the future upon touching someone. Shake decides to exploit him for loads of money while Frylock is out to prove its all fake.

episodes.name: Super Trivia
episodes.overview: Sick of losing every week at team trivia to his arch enemy, Wayne the Brain, Frylock decides to up his game. He subjects Shake and Meatwad to his special kind of tutoring and drag Carl along for the ride.

episodes.name: Universal Remonster
episodes.overview: Emory and Oglethorpe pay the Aqua Teens another visit, only this time they decide to steal their cable using the Fargate, and control what they're watching using the Universal Remonster.

episodes.name: Total Re-Carl
episodes.overview: Frylock's new invention inadvertently destroys Carl's body leaving only an infuriated head. Frylock decides to rebuild Carl's body by any means necessary which includes grave robbing and robot building.

episodes.name: Revenge of the Trees
episodes.overview: With a huge vat of oil left over from his Labor Day feast, Shake creates a foul environment in the Aqua Teen's front lawn.  With the help of Carl, the two dump the oil in the woods, but pay a hefty price in return.

episodes.name: Spirit Journey Formation Anniversary
episodes.overview: Shake puts together a metal version of the "Birthday Song" hoping to cash in on the royalties.  But, when Zakk Wylde come looking for his cut of the money, things go all wrong for Shake.

episodes.name: The Shaving
episodes.overview: It's Halloween at the Aqua Teen headquarters and a monster comes down from the attic...to get his mail. Much to his chagrin, the monster is unable to scare anyone - until he reveals a gruesome secret.

episodes.name: Broodwich
episodes.overview: Shake uncovers a delicious, demoniacally possessed submarine sandwich in his front yard. A voice tells him if he eats the whole thing, he will be killed. Shake must battle the Last Temptation of the Broodwich or lose his life.

episodes.name: Kidney Car
episodes.overview: With his prized car destroyed, Carl is left with no choice but to donate it to the Kidney Foundation.  In a bad twist of fate, the Kidney Foundation donates the car to Meatwad.

episodes.name: The Cubing
episodes.overview: The Wisdom Cube claims to hold all the known knowledge in the universe, but it seems he only possesses a knack for tiresome anecdotes. Frylock has his doubts if this is all for real.

episodes.name: Frat Aliens
episodes.overview: DP and Skeeter, fraternity brothers from outer space, get lost along the way back home and crash on earth. They quickly become unwanted and Skeeter pulls out but leaves DP behind to be handled by the Aqua Teens.

episodes.name: The Clowning
episodes.overview: Carl gets a new head of hair and doesn't wait to show it off to the Aqua Teens. However, when the hair begins to make Carl act strangely, Frylock fears the worst. Carl's been clowned!

episodes.name: The Dressing
episodes.overview: While sitting down to eat their Thanksgiving dinner one week after Thanksgiving, the Aqua Teens are interrupted by a robotic turkey who is determined to save their turkey and take it back in time in the time rift.

episodes.name: The
episodes.overview: After Shake's antics finally push him too far, Frylock leaves the Aqua Teen's house. Without Frylock around to hold him back, Shake lays waste to the house and tortures Meatwad as he never has before. Carl soon feels the effects of not having Frylock around.

episodes.name: The Cloning
episodes.overview: After breaking one too many TVs, we learn that Frylock has been cloning them the entire time.  The newest TV seems a bit off, and they find a new use for the cloning machine.

episodes.name: The Last One
episodes.overview: Several of the Aqua Teens' enemies gather on the moon to plot their next move. After a long while, things don't seem to progress and all that has been managed are the deaths of half the members.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview:
The second season of the animated television series, Aqua Teen Hunger Force originally aired in the United States on Cartoon Network's late night programming block, Adult Swim. Season two started on May 25, 2003 with "Super Birthday Snake" and ended with "The Last One" on December 31, 2003, with a total of twenty four episodes. This season continues to focus on the surreal adventures and antics of three anthropomorphic fast food items: Master Shake, Frylock, and Meatwad, who live next door to Carl Brutananadilewski in a suburban neighborhood in New Jersey.

With twenty four episodes, season two is the longest season of the series so far. Episodes in season two were written and directed by Dave Willis and Matt Maiellaro, and have either a TV-14 or a TV-PG parental rating. Almost every episode in this season features a special guest appearance, including the season finale "The Last One" which features the return several guests from the first two seasons, who have reprised their roles. This season has been made available on DVD, and other forms of home media.

episodes.name: Video Ouija
episodes.overview: Meatwad's new video game allows him to contact the dead. But by the time Shake commits suicide in order to haunt the Video Ouija realm himself, Meatwad has already lost interest in digital seances.

episodes.name: Unremarkable Voyage
episodes.overview: When Meatwad eats a very important microchip, Frylock must shrink down to retrieve it. However, while shrunk, Shake seizes the moment to capture him and shrink Carl and Meatwad. All three of them are now at Shake's mercy.

episodes.name: Mooninites 3: Remooned
episodes.overview: The Mooninites return again, only this time to cash in a check. Seeing their cash, Meatwad and Shake both try to impress the Mooninites so they get some of the dough.

episodes.name: Gee Whiz
episodes.overview: A billboard with the face of a religious icon seems to have given Meatwad the gift of a child.  Frylock doesn't trust the "pregnancy" is all it's cracked up to be.

episodes.name: EDork
episodes.overview: Shake's E-Helmet is loaded with superfluous gadgets, but somehow an add-on player piano isn't enough to satisfy his lust for convenience.

episodes.name: Little Brittle
episodes.overview: MC Pee Pants is back! Reincarnated as an old man in a retirement home, he is releasing music to get people to come visit him and, of course, Meatwad falls pray to his subliminal messages. But is there something else he wants?

episodes.name: Robositter
episodes.overview: Frylock and Shake are forced to take jobs at a restaurant in the mall and leave Meatwad under the care of Carl. Frylock comes home after their first day to find Carl had ignored Meatwad completely and that Meatwad had helped himself to the medicine cabinet. Frylock then builds a robot babysitter for Meatwad.

episodes.name: Mooninites 4: The Final Mooning
episodes.overview: Meatwad has a new video game to play. Upon beating it, the Mooninites drop in to crown him the Moon Master and call on him to help them defeat a great foe.

episodes.name: Diet
episodes.overview: With a case of beer on the line, Meatwad, Carl, and Shake all battle to see who can loose the most weight. Carl uses a special candy bar to drop pounds while Frylock makes Meatwad lose weight the manual way. Shake just works to impede the others.

episodes.name: Dusty Gozongas
episodes.overview: In an attempt to bring the Olympics to New Jersey, Shake destroys the gas line. When Frylock calls the city to fix it, they send over Dusty Gonzongas, the hottest stripper from the Wild Wild Chest club thus causing plenty of tension between Shake and Carl.

episodes.name: T-Shirt of the Living Dead
episodes.overview: An ancient and all powerful T-shirt gives Meatwad amazing powers to see and know all. Meatwad uses his new powers to summon Santa Claus and a hoard of Easter Bunnies.

episodes.name: Hypno-Germ
episodes.overview: When Hypno-Germs invade Shake's brain, they force him to do a number of insane things. Frylock uses Mexican jumping-beans to combat the germs in Shakes head with a theatrical spectacular!

episodes.name: Spacegate World
episodes.overview: When the Aqua Teens go to Panama City for a vacation, Meatwad leaves Carl to babysit Dewey, Vanessa, and Boxy Brown. At first, Carl thinks not having the Aqua Teens around is great, but soon realizes that hanging around the neighborhood by himself is a real drag.Meanwhile, in Panama City, Meatwad tries to start a comedy act, Frylock tries to get some action, and Shake loafs around the hotel room.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview:
The third season of the animated television series, Aqua Teen Hunger Force originally aired in the United States on Cartoon Network's late night programming block, Adult Swim. Season three started on April 25, 2004 with "Video Ouija" and ended with "Carl" on October 24, 2004, with a total of thirteen episodes. This season continues to focus on the surreal adventures and antics of three anthropomorphic fast food items: Master Shake, Frylock, and Meatwad, who live next door to Carl Brutananadilewski in a suburban neighborhood in New Jersey.

Season three is the only season to feature Spacecataz cold opens, in place of Dr. Weird and Steve. In season three the cold openings featuring Dr. Weird and Steve, were replaced with clips from the failed pilot Spacecataz, a potential spin-off of Aqua Teen Hunger Force. Episodes in season three were written and directed by Dave Willis and Matt Maiellaro, and have TV-14 parental rating. Almost every episode in this season features a special guest appearance, which continues a practice used in past seasons. This season has been made available on DVD, and other forms of home media.

episodes.name: Dirtfoot
episodes.overview: Shake pretends to fall down a well, where he meets the legendary New Jersey monster known as Dirtfoot.

episodes.name: Boost Mobile
episodes.overview: Shake sells himself out to Boost Mobile, and now is forced to endlessly plug the service.

episodes.name: Star Studded Xmas Spectacular (1)
episodes.overview: Master Shake reviews deleted scenes from the upcoming Aqua Teen movie.

episodes.name: Star Studded Xmas Spectacular (2)
episodes.overview: Part 2 of the deleted scenes from the Aqua Teen movie, hosted by Master Shake.

episodes.name: Dickesode
episodes.overview: Carl suffers the consequences for ordering fast food at Wong Burger. Apparently, the owner Mr. Wong has a diabolical plan.

episodes.name: Handbanana
episodes.overview: Frylock creates a genetically mutated dog for Meatwad named Handbanana, who soon begins to periodically rape Carl.

episodes.name: Party All the Time
episodes.overview: Andrew W.K. guest stars in this very special episode about tragedy, courage and ultimately, redemption.

episodes.name: Global Grilling
episodes.overview: Shake purchases an environmentally unfriendly grill.

episodes.name: Grim Reaper Gutters
episodes.overview: Clips from older shows are used. The Aqua Teens talk a lot about their past experiences. Carl goes crazy after finding out that Tara the porn star is visiting the Aqua Teens. He then runs into the grim reaper who poses as a gutter salesman.

episodes.name: Moonajuana
episodes.overview: The Mooninites get Shake and Meatwad high by burning tires. Frylock doesn't fall for this trick and later the Mooninites finally explain to him why they have been pulling all of these pranks.

episodes.name: Bart Oates
episodes.overview: Carl receives a visit from his favorite football star.

episodes.name: Antenna
episodes.overview: Frylock investigates the mysterious alien antenna built atop Carl's house. What part does professional voice artist George Lowe play in the puzzle?

episodes.name: Ezekial
episodes.overview: Shake takes on the greatest role of his life: that of a father.

episodes.name: Carl Wash
episodes.overview: Two floating brains (calling themselves Carl) hire Meatwad to advertise their dilapidated car wash. He is unable to attract customers, so with Shake's help, they get Carl to take his car in. The brains wreck his car, gas him, and remove his brain.

4.name: Season 4
4.overview: The fourth season of the animated television series, Aqua Teen Hunger Force originally aired in the United States on Cartoon Network's late night programming block, Adult Swim. Season four started on December 4, 2005 with "Dirtfoot" and ended with "Carl Wash" which originally made two unannounced stealth airings on December 22, 2006 and January 7, 2007 and later made its official debut on March 25, 2007, with a total of thirteen episodes.

episodes.name: Robots Everywhere
episodes.overview: When the Aqua Teens are chased out of there house, Carl tries to sell it. A bunch of robots move in and they are annoying Carl, and Carl is doing everything he can to stop them.

episodes.name: Sirens
episodes.overview: When a trio of sirens move in, their wanton songs pique Carl's attention.

episodes.name: Couples Skate
episodes.overview: The Aqua Teens must either escape the spider cocoons their landlord Marcula has trapped them in, or pay the rent they owe him, while Carl gets a new neighbor, a huge demon named Paul who is going through a difficult custody battle.

episodes.name: Reedickyoulus
episodes.overview: Carl's new male enhancement device produces some unsavory side effects.

episodes.name: Hoppy Bunny
episodes.overview: Carl's home becomes a haven for furries.

episodes.name: Laser Lenses
episodes.overview: Master Shake's megalomania soars to new heights once he steals Frylock's laser-shooting contact lenses.

episodes.name: Dummy Love
episodes.overview: A murderous ventriloquist dummy finds out that his favorite internal organ is the heart.

episodes.name: The Marines
episodes.overview: When Meatwad unwittingly enlists the Aqua Teens into the Marine Corps, Frylock flees the country.

episodes.name: Bible Fruit
episodes.overview: Frylock decides to party with some friends he met through a social networking website.

episodes.name: Gene E.
episodes.overview: Master Shake discovers a genie at the dump who promises to grant wishes, but instead turns the Aqua Teens invisible. After inadvertently killing him, they discover a shrunken Carl. Meatwad and Frylock try to restore their visibility, while Carl and Master Shake use their cursed states to spy on women.

episodes.name: Shake Like Me
episodes.overview: Master Shake is bitten by a radioactive black man and becomes black. Boxy Brown trys to make him a super star.

episodes.name: She Creature
episodes.overview:
A strange monster is inhabiting Carl's pool, and the Aqua Teens attempt to get to the bottom of the mystery. It turns out to be a mermaid, who has sex with Carl, Frylock, and Meatwad, who all explode as a result of being impregnated by the mermaid. Master Shake, meanwhile, does not explode, despite describing his supposed sexual encounter with the mermaid to no one, as they have exploded.

Special Guests Vincent Pastore provides the voice of Terry (uncredited) and Dana Swanson as the She Creature

episodes.name: Chick Magnet
episodes.overview: Shake buys a magnet to attract women from a TV commercial. Shake does not put in a screw that came with the magnet, so it merely brings out the feminine side of the Aqua Teens.

episodes.name: Creature From Plaque Lagoon
episodes.overview: Meatwad and Shake are set out to capture the Tooth Fairy.

episodes.name: Time Machine
episodes.overview: Frylock builds a time machine, but things don't go according to plan.

episodes.name: 2-And-A-Half Star Wars out of Five
episodes.overview: A Pink Man tries to blow up the moon. Features a full-fledged orchestral score.

episodes.name: Fry Legs
episodes.overview: Frylock begins acting strangely after falling in love with a girl.

episodes.name: Der Inflatable Fuhrer
episodes.overview: Frylock takes up some side work.

episodes.name: The Last Last One Forever and Ever
episodes.overview: The Aqua Teens find out that there is a fire in the water.

episodes.name: A PE Christmas
episodes.overview: The Aqua Teens are going to release a Christmas album, but first, they have to steal an identity!

episodes.name: Rabbot Redux
episodes.overview: After moving into their new crib, the Aqua Teens re-unite with some old friends.

episodes.name: Rubberman
episodes.overview: Carl starts raking used condoms onto the Aqua Teens' yard, giving Frylock the idea to make a duck out of them. Meatwad accidentally brings him to life but unfortunately finds him to be a bad role model.

episodes.name: Eggball
episodes.overview: Master Shake builds a pinball machine designed after himself. He runs out of pinballs, and the Aqua Teens travel to Death Island to collect pinball eggs from a flightless bird.

episodes.name: Monster
episodes.overview: Meatwad is terrified of the monsters living in the house, so Frylock tries to help him come to terms with it. Shake tries to make things worse.

episodes.name: Hands on a Hamburger
episodes.overview: The Aqua Teens compete in a contest at a suspiciously-familiar burger chain, unaware that they are pawns in Dr. Wongburger's latest scheme.

episodes.name: IAMAPOD
episodes.overview: A pod attempts to replicate Shake and then follow Chickenfoot  on the road.

episodes.name: Juggalo
episodes.overview: Guest stars the Insane Clown Posse.

10.name: Aqua TV Show Show
10.overview: Aqua TV Show Show (or ATSS) was the alternative title given to the tenth season of the animated television series, Aqua Teen Hunger Force. The tenth season aired in the United States on Cartoon Network's late night programming block, Adult Swim. The season started on August 11, 2013 with "Muscles" and ran for a total of ten episodes. This season focused on the surreal adventures and antics of three anthropomorphic fast food items: Master Shake, Frylock, and Meatwad, who live next door to Carl Brutananadilewski in a suburban neighborhood in the fictional location Seattle, New Jersey, which is completely identical to their other previous homes seen in past seasons. In episode 6 the skyline of Philadelphia is displayed in the background.
